        "creation_date": 1327375889,
        "answer_count": 2,
        "title": "Can someone explain what a Function object is in Java?",
        "body": "<blockquote>\n  <p><strong>Possible Duplicate:<\/strong><br>\n  <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/7369460/help-with-understanding-a-function-object-or-functor-in-java\">Help with understanding a function object or functor in Java<\/a>  <\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>I am currently reading the book \"data structures and problem solving using Java\" by Mark Allen Weiss and the explanation of a functor is not clear to me. <\/p>\n\n<p>1) Why do you use them?\n2) Exactly what do they do?<\/p>\n\n<p>The only thing I am getting from this book is if a particular object does not have a compareTo method you use a function object to give it one ha-ha.....help me!!<\/p>\n",
